'''Pat Proft''' (born on [[April 3]], [[1947]] in [[Wikipedia:Columbia Heights, Minnesota|Columbia Heights, Minnesota]]) is a comedy writer and actor. He began his career at Dudley Riggs' Brave New Workshop in Minneapolis. In the mid-1970s, he began writing for television and films.

He has written numerous films (many [[Wikipedia:Zucker%2C Abrahams and Zucker|ZAZ]] projects, as well as ''[[The Star Wars Holiday Special]]''), but has only directed one film (''Wrongfully Accused''), with [[Wikipedia:Leslie Nielsen|Leslie Nielsen]].

